FBIS4-13647 "drnes078dd_94004" FBIS-NES-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs Hamas Lists Conditions for `Truce' With Israel Hamas Lists Conditions for `Truce' With Israel JN2104135794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1200 GMT 21 Apr 94 JN2104135794 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Arabic BFN [Text] In Damascus, the Hamas Movement has proposed a truce with Israel to find a way out of the Palestinian crisis. In a statement issued in Damascus, Hamas Political Bureau chief Musa Abu-Marzuq said his proposal is based on the following principles: Comprehensive Israeli withdrawal from the West Bank, the Gaza Strip, and occupied Jerusalem, and the dismantling of all settlements in the occupied territories and the evacuation of the settlers. Abu-Marzuq emphasized the need to hold free and fair general elections among the Palestinian people in order to elect their leadership and representatives. He promised the Hamas Movement will respect the views of the majority.
